Description: Adaptive external pentest visibility CLI and GUI for authorized assessments
 AttackCastle is an adaptive, evidence-driven external security assessment toolkit.
 It ships a terminal-first CLI together with a Qt desktop GUI, and orchestrates
 reconnaissance, service enumeration, optional vulnerability tooling, findings
 normalization, and report generation.
 .
 This package installs the `attackcastle` command, supports launching the GUI with
 `attackcastle gui`, and recommends external scanner tooling that can be bootstrapped
 with `attackcastle doctor --install-missing` or
 `attackcastle plugins install-missing`.
